    "Similar considerations apply to protons-light blue; N protons.",
    "b, D4 polarizability versus partial charge for all the halogens in the database.",
    "The outliers were analyzed to find possible wrong atom assignments.",
    "This was the case for the bromine atom in the lower right corner, which in reality is a boron.",
    "c, Examples of inconsistent structures: 1WUG contains overly elongated NO bonds; 4MDN contains a nitrogen in angular violation of VSEPR; 5GTR shows a typical problem in the protonation state."
